<subSubSection id="9CC03AA6FF8F4834B2FEFA43D8542759" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D465692DFF8F4834B2FEFA43D8542759" blockId="5.[151,1437,1489,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="E6AEB53FFF8F4834B2FEFA43DB172481" bold="true" box="[199,335,1489,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Comments.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="0B61D78FFF8F4834B3B3FA40DBA02482" box="[394,504,1490,1513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">paratypes</typeStatus>
, including the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="ACCD29BDFF8F4834B169FA43D9E32481" box="[848,955,1489,1514]" name="Suriname" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Suriname</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="4CE175A8FF8F4834B1F5FA43DE522481" box="[972,1034,1489,1514]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1893,1914]" captionTargetBox="[174,1424,438,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1868]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Palpada panorama sp. n. male. A. Holotype, dorsal view; B. Holotype, lateral view; C. Paratype (from Suriname), dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259145/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
Fig. 
<number id="62127B0AFF8F4834B639FA43DE522481" box="[1024,1034,1489,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C), are very similar to the 
<typeStatus id="0B61D78FFF8F4834B703FA43DFC42481" box="[1338,1436,1489,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">holotype</typeStatus>
and differ only slightly in body length, ranging from 
<quantity id="1322C4C8FF8F4834B0C8FA64D9352766" box="[753,877,1526,1550]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 mm</quantity>
, and size of the yellow abdominal markings. The female sex is currently unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CC03AA6FF8F4834B2FEF9ACDBE627F6" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D465692DFF8F4834B2FEF9ACDBE627F6" blockId="5.[151,1437,1489,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="E6AEB53FFF8F4834B2FEF9ACDB16273E" bold="true" box="[199,334,1598,1621]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet (noun in apposition) is composed of the Greek words 
<emphasis id="E6AEB53FFF8F4834B6A4F9ACDEB0273E" box="[1181,1256,1598,1621]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">pantos</emphasis>
(all, the whole) and 
<emphasis id="E6AEB53FFF8F4834B2FEF9F3DB462712" box="[199,286,1633,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">horama</emphasis>
(vision, sight). It refers to the strongly enlarged ommatidia of the species, which separate it from the closely similar 
<taxonomicName id="13DA12AEFF8F4834B37BF914DBEF27F6" box="[322,439,1670,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Palpada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erratica">
<emphasis id="E6AEB53FFF8F4834B37BF914DBEF27F6" box="[322,439,1670,1693]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">P. erratica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
